./sdp/logs/Verify_T-022_20260416T043834Z_1776341500.log:397:+{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:18:33.293Z","role":"user","content":"# Task T-022@20260416T043834Z: Add live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- stable buffers expose source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, and transform history<br/>- sample banks can retain selected clips on archive storage with metadata<br/>- tests verify buffer refresh and archive path selection\n\n**Tier:** T2 — Standard (New feature / moderate refactoring)\n\n## Instructions\n\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\n\n**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\n\n### Phase 0: Explore\n- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\n- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\n- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\n- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\n\n### Phase 1: Specify\n- Write a specification to `specs/t-022@20260416t043834z-spec.md`.\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\n\n### Phase 2: Test Development\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\n\n### Phase 3: Implement\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\n- Follow existing patterns.\n\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\n\n## Rules\n\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-022@20260416T043834Z]`\n\n## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\n\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\n\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\n  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\n- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\n  foreign key relationships.\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\n  the implemented code.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun before final commit:\n```bash\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\n```\n\nAll must pass.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
./sdp/logs/Verify_T-022_20260416T043834Z_1776341500.log:408:+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:22:53.661Z","tool_name":"read_file","tool_id":"read_file_1776338573661_0","parameters":{"file_path":"progress.md","start_line":1,"end_line":100}}
./sdp/logs/Verify_T-022_20260416T043834Z_1776341500.log:416:+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:23:53.740Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776338633739_0","parameters":{"file_path":"specs/t-022@20260416t043834z-spec.md","content":"# Specification: T-022@20260416T043834Z\n\n## Problem Statement\nCypherClaw's SenseWeave requires abstractions to manage real-time environmental input (live buffers) and long-term retention of notable audio events (sample banks). We need a stable representation of the current audio buffer and a mechanism to persistently archive valuable clips with associated metadata.\n\n## Technical Approach\n1. Create a new module `my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`.\n2. Define a `LiveBuffer` class that exposes `source_name`, `capture_path`, `freshness`, `rms`, `spectral_profile`, and `transform_history`. Provide a method to refresh this state from new sensory data.\n3. Define a `SampleBankStorage` (or `SampleArchive`) class representing the \"sample bank\" abstraction. It will handle copying/moving selected clips to an archive directory and storing associated metadata (e.g., as JSON files side-by-side with the audio).\n4. Create comprehensive tests in `tests/test_live_buffer.py` to ensure `LiveBuffer` state updates correctly upon refresh, and that `SampleBankStorage` accurately selects archive paths and persists metadata.\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Missing source files during retention (should gracefully fail or return `None`).\n- Empty spectral profiles or missing RMS values on refresh (should default to zeros or retain previous valid values based on the semantics).\n- Metadata persistence formatting and safety.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- stable buffers expose source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, and transform history\n  - VERIFY: `grep -q \"class LiveBuffer\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`\n- sample banks can retain selected clips on archive storage with metadata\n  - VERIFY: `grep -q \"def retain_clip\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`\n- tests verify buffer refresh and archive path selection\n  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_live_buffer.py -x`\n"}}
./sdp/logs/Verify_T-022_20260416T043834Z_1776341500.log:428:+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:37:56.363Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776339476363_0","parameters":{"file_path":"my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py","content":"\"\"\"Live buffer and sample bank archive abstractions for SenseWeave.\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport shutil\nimport time\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass LiveBuffer:\n    \"\"\"State representation of a continuous environmental audio buffer.\"\"\"\n    source_name: str\n    capture_path: str\n    freshness: float = 0.0\n    rms: float = 0.0\n    spectral_profile: dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=dict)\n    transform_history: tuple[str, ...] = ()\n\n    def refresh(\n        self,\n        freshness: float,\n        rms: float,\n        spectral_profile: dict[str, float],\n        transform_history: tuple[str, ...],\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update the buffer state with recent sensory data.\"\"\"\n        self.freshness = freshness\n        self.rms = rms\n        self.spectral_profile = dict(spectral_profile)\n        self.transform_history = tuple(transform_history)\n\n\nclass SampleBankArchive:\n    \"\"\"Manages the long-term retention of selected clips.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, archive_dir: Path | str):\n        self.archive_dir = Path(archive_dir)\n        self.archive_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    def retain_clip(self, source_path: Path | str, source_name: str, metadata: dict[str, Any]) -> Path | None:\n        \"\"\"\n        Copy a clip to the archive storage along with its metadata.\n        \n        Args:\n            source_path: Path to the audio file to retain.\n            source_name: The name of the SenseWeave source (e.g., 'room_mic').\n            metadata: Associated metadata to persist alongside the file.\n            \n        Returns:\n            The Path to the archived audio file, or None if the source file was missing.\n        \"\"\"\n        source = Path(source_path)\n        if not source.exists():\n            return None\n\n        # Create source-specific subdirectory\n        source_dir = self.archive_dir / source_name\n        source_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n        # Generate a unique name based on timestamp\n        timestamp = int(time.time() * 1000)\n        unique_id = f\"{source_name}_{timestamp}\"\n        \n        dest_audio = source_dir / f\"{unique_id}{source.suffix}\"\n        dest_meta = source_dir / f\"{unique_id}.json\"\n\n        # Copy audio file\n        shutil.copy2(source, dest_audio)\n\n        # Save metadata\n        meta_to_save = dict(metadata)\n        if \"timestamp\" not in meta_to_save:\n            meta_to_save[\"timestamp\"] = timestamp\n            \n        dest_meta.write_text(json.dumps(meta_to_save, indent=2))\n\n        return dest_audio\n"}}
